# gas-best-practices — Cursor rules

When working with Google Apps Script code (`.gs` files, `appsscript.json`, `.clasp.json`, or
mentions of GAS/clasp), follow the rules in `rules/` of this repo.

Trigger detection — apply when:
- Files with `.gs` extension exist
- `appsscript.json` or `.clasp.json` in project root
- Code references `SpreadsheetApp`, `DriveApp`, `HtmlService`, `UrlFetchApp`, `LockService`, etc.
- HTML files use `google.script.run`

## Core principles

1. Every server function returns a `{ok, message/data}` envelope — never throw to client
2. Read sheets once with `getDataRange().getValues()` but write per-cell if merged cells possible
3. Lazy resource creation (folders, sheets, columns) on startup via Config sheet
4. Cache user lookups via `CacheService.getScriptCache()` with explicit invalidation
5. `LockService.getScriptLock()` around concurrent mutations + try/finally release
6. Thai user-facing messages, English Logger.log
7. Log every RPC boundary (console.log client + Logger.log server)
8. Force text format for leading-zero numeric fields (phone, ID, postal code)
9. Recompute critical values server-side — never trust client

